        title: 'The Retranslation Question',
        html: '<p>The War of the Lions script by Joseph Reeder and Tom Slattery is, by any technical measure, vastly better: accurate, coherent, and written in a deliberately Shakespearean register that suits the material. It is also, to a large constituency of players, wrong — because the broken 1997 script is the one they experienced, and its errors have become inseparable from their memory of the game.</p><p>This puts Tactics in an odd category alongside Ted Woolsey\'s Square work: a localisation whose defects are now load-bearing cultural artefacts. "Blame yourself or God" is a mistranslation and it is also, at this point, one of the most quoted lines in the series. Fixing it was unquestionably correct, and something was unquestionably lost — which is roughly the permanent condition of game localisation.</p>',
